---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  lang="en"
  title="DTS | YWAM Sendai"
  description="Discipleship Training School (DTS) at YWAM Sendai is a foundational season of discipleship, community life, and mission in Sendai, Japan."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="stack">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Discipleship Training School</p>
          <h1 class="hero-title max-w-title">
            A foundational season of discipleship, formation, and mission.
          </h1>
        </div>

        <p class="lead">
          DTS at YWAM Sendai is a full-time school designed to help students know
          God more deeply, grow in Christian character, and respond to His call
          through teaching, prayer, community life, and outreach.
        </p>

        <div class="btn-group">
          <button type="button" class="btn-primary open-hub-trigger">Ask AI</button>
          <a href="/en/apply" class="btn-secondary-dark">Apply</a>
          <a
            href="https://guide.ywamsendai.org/en"
            class="btn-secondary-dark"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Visit Handbook
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="text-inverse-soft mb-0">
          Ask about DTS, dates, costs, expectations, or whether this school may be a good fit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card hero-feature-card stack-sm">
        <p class="eyebrow">Quick Overview</p>
        <h2 class="card-title">What DTS is</h2>
        <p>
          DTS is the foundational training school of YWAM and a prerequisite for
          many future YWAM pathways, including long-term staff service.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-4">
        <article class="card">
          <h2 class="card-title">Length</h2>
          <p>About 5 to 6 months</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2 class="card-title">Structure</h2>
          <p>Lecture phase + outreach phase</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2 class="card-title">Focus</h2>
          <p>Discipleship, community life, and mission</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card surface-accent-soft">
          <h2 class="card-title">Role in YWAM</h2>
          <p>Foundational school and prerequisite for staff</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">What is DTS?</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">
          More than a course. A live-learn environment for discipleship.
        </h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DTS stands for Discipleship Training School. It is the entry-level school
          of YWAM and is designed to help students build a foundation for life with God,
          Christian character, and participation in mission.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Know God</h3>
          <p>Grow in relationship with God through Scripture, prayer, worship, and obedience.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Be formed in community</h3>
          <p>Learn through shared life, mentoring, practical service, and discipleship.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Participate in mission</h3>
          <p>Put learning into practice through outreach, service, and team-based ministry.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2" style="align-items: start;">
        <div class="stack-sm">
          <p class="eyebrow">DTS at YWAM Sendai</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Shaped by life in Sendai and the wider Tohoku region</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            DTS at YWAM Sendai includes the core YWAM framework, but it is also shaped
            by the local context of Japan, community-based mission, and long-term faithful presence.
          </p>
          <p class="text-soft">
            Students should expect not only biblical teaching and discipleship, but also
            formation connected to cultural humility, prayerful presence, relationships,
            and service rooted in place.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid stack-sm">
          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Life in Japan</h3>
            <p>Formation shaped by real life in a Japanese context.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Cultural humility</h3>
            <p>Learning to listen, adapt, and serve with respect.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Prayerful presence</h3>
            <p>Mission rooted in faithfulness, relationship, and place.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Bilingual environment</h3>
            <p>Participation shaped by both English and Japanese learning rhythms.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Structure</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Two phases that work together</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DTS includes a lecture phase and an outreach phase. The first builds foundations;
          the second puts learning into practice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="card">
          <span class="chip-accent">Phase 1</span>
          <h3 class="card-title">Lecture Phase</h3>
          <p>
            The lecture phase focuses on biblical teaching, discipleship, worship,
            prayer, community life, and personal formation.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li>Classroom teaching</li>
            <li>Small-group processing</li>
            <li>Personal reflection</li>
            <li>Worship and intercession</li>
            <li>One-on-one mentoring</li>
            <li>Practical service and shared responsibilities</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="chip-accent">Phase 2</span>
          <h3 class="card-title">Outreach Phase</h3>
          <p>
            The outreach phase gives students the opportunity to live out what they
            have been learning through team-based ministry in real contexts.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li>Evangelism and discipleship</li>
            <li>Mercy ministry and practical service</li>
            <li>Church partnership</li>
            <li>Cross-cultural ministry</li>
            <li>Team life, prayer, and debriefing</li>
            <li>Flexibility and dependence on God</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">What students can expect</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">A season that is both stretching and deeply formative</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DTS is not only about receiving information. It is a full-time season of participation,
          responsibility, growth, and discipleship.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Shared rhythms</h3>
          <p>Community life, worship, intercession, mentoring, and practical responsibilities.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Personal growth</h3>
          <p>Challenge, maturity, correction, surrender, and growth in Christian character.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Mission readiness</h3>
          <p>Preparation for outreach, teamwork, service, and practical obedience.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who is DTS for?</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">For those seeking a foundation in discipleship and mission</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DTS is often a good fit for people who want focused time to grow in their relationship
          with God, be discipled in Christian community, and discern their next step.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card-dark">
          <h3 class="card-title">Grow with God</h3>
          <p>For those who want to know God more deeply and hear His voice more clearly.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card-dark">
          <h3 class="card-title">Be discipled</h3>
          <p>For those who want formation in community, character, and obedience.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card-dark">
          <h3 class="card-title">Prepare for what’s next</h3>
          <p>For those exploring future ministry, training, or long-term service in YWAM.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper border-top">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Dates and Costs</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Practical information for the upcoming DTS</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Specific schedules and outreach details may vary, but the following dates and current estimates
          provide a general picture for planning.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2" style="align-items: start;">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Dates</h3>
          <div class="stack-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Arrival Day</p>
              <p>24 September 2026</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Graduation Day</p>
              <p>5 March 2027</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Estimated Costs</h3>
          <div class="stack-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Tuition</p>
              <p>¥300,000</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Accommodation</p>
              <p>¥120,000</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Food and local transportation</p>
              <p>¥150,000 estimated</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Outreach phase</p>
              <p>¥400,000 estimated</p>
            </div>
            <div class="surface-accent rounded-md p-lg">
              <p class="eyebrow">Estimated total</p>
              <p><strong>¥970,000</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="container-narrow" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <p class="text-soft">
          Tuition includes lectures, speaker and teacher-related transport, speaker and teacher-related
          food and accommodation, and administrative costs. Accommodation includes wifi, utilities,
          and shared household consumables. Outreach costs vary depending on destination and travel expenses.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container container-narrow center stack">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Next Step</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Interested in DTS?</h2>
        <p class="lead mx-auto">
          If you are exploring DTS, discerning your next season, or wondering whether this school may be a good fit,
          we would love to help you take the next step.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
        <button type="button" class="btn-primary open-hub-trigger">Ask AI</button>
        <a href="/en/apply" class="btn-secondary">Apply</a>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
        <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-text">Contact</a>
        <a
          href="https://guide.ywamsendai.org/en"
          class="btn-text"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Visit Handbook
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>